definition.value: A member of the class of monofluorobenzenes that is benzene substituted by 5-amino-4-cyano-1H-imidazol-1-yl, fluoro, and morpholin-4-yl groups at positions 1, 3 and 4, respectively.

A member of the clas of purines that is 9H-purine substituted by 3,4-dimethoxyphenyl, aminocarbonyl, and 4-(4-methylpiperazin-1-yl)-3-nitrophenyl groups at positions 2, 6 and 9, respectively. It is an inhibitor of EGFR and a potential anticancer agent.
